<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,725,1274]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,320,1098,1124]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Remarks.</emphasis>
In some specimens the coloration of the setae is bright orange, although setal coloration varies from orange to white (see 
<figureCitation box="[463,547,1136,1162]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="13.[151,274,1360,1384]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,194,1326]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,194,1338]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Head, anterior view. 25. Sphaeropthalma. megagnathos; 26. S. mendica; 27. S. pallida; 28. S. sublobata; 29. S. tetracuspis; 30. S. triangularis; and 31. S. yumaella." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196850/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[518,547,1136,1162]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.366" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="in" value="29.0">29</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Pitts" box="[586,718,1136,1162]" pageId="25" pageNumber="34" refString="Pitts, J. P. (2006) Review of the Sphaeropthalma imperialis species-group (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae), with descriptions of females and taxonomic notes. Zootaxa, 1248, 1 - 20." type="journal article" year="2006">
Pitts, 
<number box="[654,718,1136,1162]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The orangish specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[1064,1250,1136,1161]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megagnathos">
<emphasis box="[1064,1250,1136,1161]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">S. megagnathos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could easily be confused with 
<taxonomicName box="[326,442,1173,1198]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luiseno">
<emphasis box="[326,442,1173,1198]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">S. luiseno</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName box="[483,627,1173,1198]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contracta">
<emphasis box="[483,627,1173,1198]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">S. contracta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on coloration. They do not occur in Deep Canyon; 
<taxonomicName box="[1320,1435,1173,1198]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luiseno">
<emphasis box="[1320,1435,1173,1198]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">S. luiseno</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has large projections bearing long, curved setae on the middle and hind coxae, while 
<taxonomicName box="[1170,1314,1211,1236]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contracta">
<emphasis box="[1170,1314,1211,1236]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">S. contracta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has much smaller ocelli and different genitalic morphology (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Pitts" box="[788,977,1248,1274]" pageId="25" pageNumber="34" refString="Pitts, J. P., Parker, F. D. &amp; Pitts-Singer, T. L. (2004) A review of the Sphaeropthalma uro species-group (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae), with taxonomic changes. Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 77, 223 - 234." type="journal article" year="2004">
Pitts 
<emphasis box="[847,906,1248,1273]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[913,977,1248,1274]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
